metatags.og:description: Online posts claim that vitamin C can "stop" the new coronavirus. While it's true that vitamin C can have a marginal effect on warding off a cold, there's no evidence that it can stop or treat the new coronavirus.

metatags.og:description: President Donald Trump has enthusiastically pushed the use of two malaria drugs -- one in combination with an antibiotic -- to treat COVID-19, the disease caused by the novel coronavirus. But there is currently only limited evidence to suggest the drugs are effective against the new virus.
